Federal Home Loan Bank of Boston Key Developments

Federal Home Loan Bank of Boston Declares Cash Dividend for the First Quarter of 2017, Payable on May 2, 2017
Apr 19 17
Federal Home Loan Bank of Boston's board of directors declared a dividend equal to an annual yield of 4.08%, the approximate daily average three-month LIBOR yield for the first quarter of 2017 plus 300 basis points. The dividend, based on average stock outstanding for the first quarter of 2017, will be paid on May 2, 2017.


Federal Home Loan Bank of Boston Reports Unaudited Earnings Results for the First Quarter Ended March 31, 2017
Apr 19 17
Federal Home Loan Bank of Boston reported unaudited earnings results for the first quarter ended March 31, 2017. For the quarter, the company reported net interest income of $62,504,000 against $56,104,000 a year ago. Net income was $37,398,000 against $29,502,000 a year ago. Return on average assets was 0.25% against 0.20% a year ago. Return on average equity was 4.56% against 3.88% a year ago.


